1 olive oil
1 Brown Onion
½ tin Crushed & Sieved Tomatoes
¼ tsp salt
1 tsp brown sugar
20 g butter
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ tbs balsamic vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 bag baby broccoli
2 clove garlic
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 tomato
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
½ tbs plain flour
1 egg

• Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Trim baby broccoli and cut into bite-sized
pieces. Cut onion into wedges.
• Place baby broccoli and onion on a lined oven
tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt
and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly,
then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. Set aside
to cool slightly.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic.
• In a small saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium heat. Cook garlic until fragrant,
1 minute.
• Add crushed & sieved tomatoes (see
ingredients), the salt, brown sugar and the
butter and stir to combine. Reduce heat to low,
then simmer, stirring occasionally, 5-6 minutes.

• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour,
garlic & herb seasoning and a pinch of salt.
• In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg.
• In a third shallow bowl, place panko
breadcrumbs.
• Dip chicken breast strips into the flour mixture,
followed by the egg, and finally in panko
breadcrumbs. Set aside on a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with enough olive oil to coat the base. When
oil is hot, cook chicken until golden, 2 minutes
each side.
• Place chicken on a second lined oven tray.
• Top each piece with the tomato sauce and sprinkle over the shredded Cheddar cheese. Season with salt.
• Bake chicken until cooked through,
8-10 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

Little cooks: Kids can add the finishing touch by
sprinkling the cheese on top.

• Meanwhile, cut tomato into small chunks.
• In a large bowl, combine the balsamic vinegar,
some olive oil (1 tbs for 2 people / 2 tbs for 4
people) and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add the
roasted veggies, tomato and salad leaves to
the dressing. Toss to coat.

Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!

• Divide garlic and herb crumbed chicken
parmigiana between plates.
• Serve with roasted veggie and tomato salad.
Enjoy!